                    "short_description":  "India’s largest earth dam and one of Wayanad’s most popular tourist attractions, built in 1979 as part of the Kuttiyadi Hydroelectric Project.",
                    "detailed":  "Banasura Sagar Dam was constructed in 1979 as part of the Kuttiyadi Augmentation Scheme to support hydroelectric power generation and irrigation. Built using layers of huge stones and soil, it is classified as an earth dam—the largest in India and second largest in Asia. Over the years, the dam’s reservoir formed several small islets, making it a key eco-tourism spot. The region is part of the Western Ghats UNESCO Biosphere Reserve, popular for boating, trekking, and nature photography."
